HEADWORD: Pseudomorphism
<hw>Pseu`do*mor"phism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>The state of having, or the property of
taking, a crystalline form unlike that which belongs to the
species.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pseudomorphous</ent>⟦br⟧
